President Barack Obama announced his intent to nominate General Charles Bolden as Administrator of NASA and Lori Garver as Deputy Administrator of NASA. General Bolden is a retired United States Marine Corps officer and is currently the CEO of a military and aerospace consulting firm. He has a background in aviation and has served as an astronaut, flying multiple space shuttle missions. Lori Garver has experience in space policy and management consulting, and has previously served as NASA's Associate Administrator of the Office of Policy and Plans. Both nominees have the expertise to help NASA advance in science, aeronautics, and exploration in the 21st century.